                                <persName type="standard" xml:lang="ja-Latn">Ōtsuki Genkan</persName>
                                <note>Ōtsuki Genkan spent some years studying Dutch in Nagasaki and
                                    progressed far enough with the language to be able to write a
                                    grammar of Dutch. After spending some years as the Sendai domain
                                    doctor, he was employed by the Bakufu government as a translator
                                    of imported books.</note>
